  line 1
  line `THE ADVOCATES ’ WELFARE FUND ACT, 2001`
  line __________
  line `ARRANGEMENT OF SECTIONS`
  line __________
  line `CHAPTER I`
  line `P RELIMINARY`
  line `S ECTIONS`
  line `1. Short title, extent and commencement.`
  line `2. Definitions.`
  line `CHAPTER II`
  line `C ONSTITUTION OF A DVOCATES’ W ELFARE F UND`
  line `3. Advocates’ Welfare Fund.`
  line `CHAPTER III`
  line `E STABLISHMENT OF T RUSTEE C OMMITTEE`
  line `4. Establishment of Trustee Committee.`
  line `5. Disqualifications and removal o f Chairperson o r Member of Trustee Committee.`
  line `6. Resignation by nominated Chairperson and Members of Trustee Committee and fi l ling up of`
  line `casual vacancy.`
  line `7. Vac ancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings of Trustee Committee.`
  line `8. Meetings of Trustee Committee.`
  line `9. Travelling and daily allowances to nominated Chairperson and Members of Trustee Committee.`
  line `10. Vesting and application of Fund.`
  line `11. Functions of Trustee Committee.`
  line `12. Bor rowing and investment.`
  line `13. Accounts and audit.`
  line `14. Powers and duties of Secretary.`
  line `15. Payment of certain monies to Fund by State Bar Council.`
  line `CHAPTER IV`
  line `R ECOGNITION OF ANY ASSOCIATION OF ADVOCATES`
  line `16. Recognition by a State Bar Council of any association of advocates.`
  line `17. Duties of State Bar Associations and State Advocates’ Associations.`
  line `CHAPTER V`
  line `M EMBERSHIP AND PAYMENT OUT OF A DVOCATES’ W ELFARE F UND`
  line `18. Membership in Fund.`
  line `19. Ex gratia grant to a member of Fund.`
  line `20. Review.`
  line `21. Payment of amount on cessation of practice.`
  line `22. Restriction on alienation, attachment, etc., of interest of member in Fund.`
  line `23. Exemption from income - tax.`
  line `24. Group Life Insurance for members of Fund and other benefits.`
  line `25. Appeal against decision or order of Trustee Committee.`
