obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line 3
  line `THE ADVOCATES ’ WELFARE FUND ACT, 2001`
  line `A CT N O. 45 OF 2001`
  line `[14 th September, 2001.]`
  line `An Act to provide for the constitution of a welfare fund for the benefit of advocates and for`
  line `matters connected therewith or incidental thereto.`
  line `B E it enacted by Parliament in the Fifty - second Year of the Republic of India as follows: —`
  line `CHAPTER I`
  line `P RELIMINARY`
  line `1. Short t itle, extent and commencement. — ( 1 ) This Act may be called the Adv ocates’ Welfare`
  line `Fund Act, 2001.`
  line `( 2 ) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line `( 3 ) It shall come into force on such date 1 as the Central Government may, by notification, appoint;`
  line `and different dates may be appointed for different provision s of this Act and for different States, and any`
  line `reference in any such provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed in relation to any`
  line `State as a reference to the coming into force o f that provision in that State.`
  line `2. Definitions. — In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `( a ) “advocate” means an advocate whose name has been entered in the State roll prepared and`
  line `maintained by a State Bar Council under section 17 of the Advocates Act, 1961 (25 of 1961) and who`
  line `is a member of a State Bar Association or State Advocates’ Asso ciation;`
  line `( b ) “ appropriate Government” means, —`
  line `( i ) in the case of advocates admitted on the roll of a Bar Council of a State, the State`
  line Government;
  line `( ii ) in the case of advocates admitted on the roll of a Bar Council of a Union ter ritory, the`
  line `Central Government;`
  line `( c ) “cessation of practice” means removal of the name of an advocate from the State roll under`
  line `section 26A of the Ad vocates Act, 1961 (25 of 19 61);`
  line `( d ) “Chairperson” means the Chairperson of the Trustee Committee referred to in clause ( a ) of`
  line `sub - section ( 3 ) of section 4;`
  line `( e ) “chartered accoun tant” means a chartered accountant as defined in clause ( b ) of`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ) of section 2 of the Chartered Accountants Act, 1949 (38 of 1949) and who has`
  line `obtained a certificate of practice under sub - section ( 1 ) of section 6 of that Act;`
  line `( f ) “dependants” means the spouse, parents or minor ch ildren of a member of the Fund;`
  line `( g ) “Fund” means the Advocates’ Welfare Fund constituted under sub - section ( 1 ) of section 3;`
  line `( h ) “insurer” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( 9 ) of section 2 of the I nsurance`
  line `Act, 1938 (4 of 1938);`
  line `( i ) “member of the Fund” means an advocate admitted to the benefits of the Fund and who`
  line `continues to be a member thereof un der the provisions of this Act;`
  line `( j ) “notification” means a notification published in the Official Gazette of the appropriate`
  line `Government and the expression “notified” shall be construed accordingly;`
  line `( k ) “prescribed” means prescribed by rules ma de under this Act;`
  line `( l ) “Schedule ” means a Schedule to this Act;`
  line `( m ) “scheduled bank” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( e ) of section 2 of the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1 934);`
  line `1. 1st November, 2001 (whole of India except certain States), vide notification No. S.O. 946( E ), dated 26th September, 2001, see`
  line `Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3( ii ).`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-4
  sectionNo (4)
