  title `Page 4`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  sourcePage 4
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line 4
  line `( n ) “stamp” means the Advocates’ Welfare Fund Stamp printed an d distributed under`
  line `section 26;`
  line `( o ) “State” means a State specified in the First Schedule to the Constitution and s hall include a`
  line `Union territory;`
  line `( p ) “State Advocates’ Association” means an association of advocates in a State recognised by`
  line `the Bar Council of that State under section 16;`
  line `( q ) “State Bar Association” means an association of advocates recognised by the Bar Council of`
  line `that State under section 16;`
  line `( r ) “Sta te Bar Council” means a Bar Council referred to in section 3 of the Ad vocates`
  line `Act, 1961 (25 of 1961);`
  line `( s ) “suspension of practice” means voluntary suspension of practice as an advocate or suspension`
  line `of an advocate by a St ate Bar Council for misconduct;`
  line `( t ) “Trustee Committee” means the Advocates’ Welfare Fun d Trustee Committee established`
  line `under sub - section ( 1 ) of section 4;`
  line `( u ) “Vakalatnama” includes memorandum of appearance or any other document by which an`
  line `advocate is empowered to appear or plead before a ny court, tribunal or other authority;`
  line `( v ) words and expressions used and not defined in this Act but defined in the A dvocates`
  line `Act, 1961 (25 of 1961) shall have the meanings respectivel y assigned to them in that Act.`
  line `CHAPTER II`
  line `C ONSTITUTION OF A DVOCATES’ W ELFARE F UND`
  line `3. Advocates’ Welfare Fund. — ( 1 ) The appropriate Government shall constitute a fund to be called`
  line `the “Advocates’ Welfare Fund”.`
  line `( 2 ) There shall be credited to the Fund —`
  line `( a ) all amounts paid by a Stat e Bar Council under section 15;`
  line `( b ) any other contribution made by a State Bar Counci l;`
  line `( c ) any voluntary donation or contribution made t o the Fund by the Bar Council of India, any`
  line `State Bar Association, any State Advocates’ Association or other association or institution, or any`
  line `advocat e or other person;`
  line `( d ) any grant which may be made b y the Central Government or a State Government to the Fund`
  line `after due app ropriation made in this behalf;`
  line `( e ) any sums borrowed under section 12;`
  line `( f ) all s ums collected under section 18;`
  line `( g ) all sums received from the Life Insurance Corporation of India or any other insurer on the`
  line `death of any member of the Fund un der any Group Insurance Policy;`
  line `( h ) any profit or dividend or refund received from the Life Insurance Corporation of India or any`
  line `other insurer in respect of policies of Group Insura nce of the members of the Fund;`
  line `( i ) any interest or dividend or other return on any investment ma de out of any part of the Fund;`
  line `( j ) all sums collected by way of s ale of stamps under section 26.`
  line `( 3 ) The sums specified in sub - section ( 2 ) shall be paid to, or collected by, such agencies, at such`
  line `intervals and in suc h manner, as may be prescribed.`
  line `CHAPTER III`
  line `E STABLISHMENT OF T RUSTEE C OMMITTEE`
  line `4. Establishment of Trustee Committee. — ( 1 ) With effect from such date as the appropriate`
  line `Government may, by notification, appoint in this behalf, there shall be established a Trustee Committee to`
  line `be called the “Advocates’ W elfare Fund Trustee Committee”.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-5
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Page 5`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  sourcePage 5
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line 5
  line `( 2 ) The Trustee Committee shall be a body corporate having perpetual succession and a common seal`
  line `with power to acquire, hold and dispose of property and shall, by the said name, sue and be sued.`
  line `( 3 ) The Trustee Committee shall consist of —`
  line `( a ) the Advocate - General of a State - Chairperson, ex officio:`
  line `Provided that where there is no Advocate - General of a State, the appropriate Government shall`
  line `nominate a seni or advocate to be the C hairperson;`
  line `( b ) the Secretary to the appropriate Government in`
  line `its Law Department or M inistry`
  line `- Member, ex officio;`
  line `( c ) the Secretary to the appropriate Government in`
  line `its Home Department or Ministry`
  line `- Member, ex officio;`
  line `( d ) the Chairman of the State Bar Council - Member, ex officio;`
  line `( e ) the Government Pleader or the Public`
  line `Prosecutor, as may be nominated by the`
  line `appropriate Government`
  line `- Member;`
  line `( f ) two advocates to be nominated by the State Bar`
  line Council
  line `- Member s;`
  line `( g ) the Secretary of the State Bar Council - Secretary, ex officio.`
  line `( 4 ) The Chairperson nominated under the proviso to clause ( a ) of sub - section ( 3 ) shall hold office for`
  line `a period not exceeding three years from the date on which he enters upon his office.`
  line `( 5 ) Every Member of the Trustee Committee nominated under clause ( e ) or clause ( f ) of`
  line `sub - section ( 3 ) shall hold office for a period not e xceeding three years from the date on w hich he enters`
  line `upon his office.`
  line `5. Disqualifications and removal of Chairperson or Member of Trustee Committee. — ( 1 ) The`
  line `appropriate Government shall remove from office the Chairperson or any Member of the Trustee`
  line `Committee, who —`
  line `( a ) is, or at any time has bee n, adjudged as an insolvent; or`
  line `( b ) has become physically or mentally incapable of acting as the Chairperson or a Memb er of the`
  line `Trustee Committee; or`
  line `( c ) has been convicted of an offence which, in the opinion o f the appropriate Governmen t,`
  line `involves moral turpitude; or`
  line `( d ) has acquired such financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially his functions as`
  line `the Chairperson or a Memb er of the Trustee Committee; or`
  line `( e ) has so abused his position as to render his continuation in office detrime ntal to the public`
  line `interest; or`
  line `( f ) is, or at any tim e has been, absent without leave of the Trustee Committee for more than three`
  line `consecutive meetings of the Trustee Committee:`
  line `Provided that the Trustee Committee may, on sufficient ground, condone the absence of such`
  line `Chairperson or Member.`
  line `( 2 ) No such Chairperson or Member of the Trustee Committee shall be removed under clause ( d ) or`
  line `clause ( e ) of sub - section ( 1 ) unless he has been given a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line `6. Resignation by nominated Chairperson and Members of Trustee Committee and filling up of`
  line `casual vacancy. — ( 1 ) The Chairperson referred to in sub - section ( 4 ) of section 4 or a Mem ber nominated`
  line `under clause ( e ) of sub - section ( 3 ) of that section may resign his office by giving three months’ notice in`
  line `writing to the appropriate Government and on such resignation being accepted by the appropriate`
  line `Government such Chairperson or Member shall vacate his office.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-6
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Page 6`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  sourcePage 6
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line 6
  line `( 2 ) A Member nominated under clause ( f ) of sub - section ( 3 ) of section 4 may resign his office by`
  line `giving three months’ notice in writing to the State Bar Council and on such resignation being accepted by`
  line `the State Bar Council such Member shall vacate his office.`
  line `( 3 ) A casual vacancy in the office of the Chairperson or a Member referred to in sub - section ( 1 ) who`
  line `has resigned may be filled up, as soon as may be, by the appropriate Government and the Chairperson or`
  line `a Member so nominated shall hold office only so long as the Chairperson or the Member in whose place`
  line `he is nominated would have been entitled to hold offic e if the vacancy did not occur.`
  line `( 4 ) A casual vacancy in the office of a Member referred to in su b - section ( 2 ) who has resigned may`
  line `be filled up, as soon as may be, by the State Bar Council and a Member so nominated shall hold office`
  line `only so long as the Member in whose place he is nominated would have been entitled to hold offic e if the`
  line `vacancy did no t occur.`
  line `7. Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings of Trustee Committee. — No act or proceeding of`
  line `the Trustee Committee shall be invalid merely by reason of —`
  line `( a ) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitutio n of, the Trustee Committee; or`
  line `( b ) any defect or irregularity in the nomination of a person acting as the Chairperson or a Memb er`
  line `of the Trustee Committee; or`
  line `( c ) any irregularity in the procedure of the Trustee Committee not af fecting the merits of the case.`
  line `8. Meetings of Trustee Comm ittee. — ( 1 ) The Trustee Committee shall meet at least once in every`
  line `three calendar months and at least four such meetings shall be held in every year to transact business`
  line `under this Act and the rules made thereunder.`
  line `( 2 ) Three Members of the Trustee Committee shall form the quorum for a me eting of the Trustee`
  line Committee.
  line `( 3 ) The Chairperson of the Trustee Committee or, if for any reason, he is unable to attend a meeting`
  line `of the Trustee Committee, any other Member chosen by the Members of the Trustee Committee present`
  line `from amongst themselves at the meetin g shall preside at the meeting.`
  line `( 4 ) All questions which come up in a meeting of the Trustee Committee shall be decided by a`
  line `majority vote of the Members of the Trustee Committee present and voting, and, in the event of an`
  line `equality of vot es, the Chairperson, or in his absence, the Member of the Trustee Committee presiding,`
  line `shall have a second or casting vote.`
  line `9. Travelling and daily allowances to nominated Chairperson and Members of Trust ee`
  line `Committee. — The Chairperson referred to in sub - section ( 4 ) of section 4 and Members of the Trustee`
  line `Committee referred to in clauses ( e ) and ( f ) of sub - section ( 3 ) of that section shall be entitled to be paid`
  line `such travelling and daily allowances as are ad missible to the members of the State Bar Council.`
  line `10. Vesting and application of Fund. — The Fund shall vest in, and be held and applied by, the`
  line `Trustee Committee subject to the provisions, and for the purp oses, of this Act.`
  line `11. Functions of Trustee Committee. — ( 1 ) Subject to the provisions of this Act and any other law`
  line `for the time being in force, the Tru stee Commi ttee shall administer the Fund.`
  line `( 2 ) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions contained in sub - section ( 1 ), the Trustee`
  line `Committee shall —`
  line `( a ) hold the amounts and assets bel onging to the Fund in trust;`
  line `( b ) receive applications for admission or re - admission as members to the Fund, and dispose of`
  line `such applications within ninety days fr om the date of receipt thereof;`
  line `( c ) receive applications from the members of the Fund, their nominees or legal heirs, as the case`
  line `may be, for payment out of the Fund, conduct such enquiry as it deems necessary and dispose of the`
  line `applications within five months fr om the date of receipt there of;`
  line `( d ) record in the minutes book of the Trustee Committee, its decisions on the applications;`
  line `( e ) pay to the members of the Fund or their nominees or le gal heirs, as the case may be, the`
  line `amounts at the rates specified in Schedule I;`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-7
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Page 7`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  sourcePage 7
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line 7
  line `( f ) send such periodical and annual reports as may be prescribed, to the appropriate Govern ment`
  line `and the State Bar Council;`
  line `( g ) communicate to the applicants, by registered post with acknowledgment due or through`
  line `electronic mode, the decisions of the Trustee Committee in respect of applications for admission or`
  line `re - admission as members to the Fund or cla ims to the benefit of the Fund;`
  line `( h ) do such other acts as are, or may be, required to be done under this Act and the rules made`
  line thereunder.
  line `12. Borrowing and investment. — ( 1 ) The Trustee Committee may, with the prior approval of the`
  line `appropriate Government and the State Bar Council, borrow, from time to time, any sum required f or`
  line `carryin g out the purposes of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) The Trustee Committee shall deposit all monies and receipts forming part of the Fund in any`
  line `scheduled bank or invest the same in debt instruments of any corp oration owned or controlled by the`
  line `appropriate Government or in loans floated by the appropriate Government or in any other manner as the`
  line `State Bar Council may, from time to time, direct with the prior approval of the appropriate Government.`
  line `( 3 ) All amounts due and payable under this Act and all expenditure relating to the management and`
  line `administration of the Fund shall be paid out of the Fund.`
  line `13. Accoun ts and audit. — ( 1 ) The Trustee Committee shall maintain proper accounts and other`
  line `relevant records and prepare an annual statement of accounts and annual report in such form and in su ch`
  line `manner as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 2 ) The accounts of the Trustee Committee shall be audited annually by a chartered accountant`
  line `appo inted by the State Bar Council.`
  line `( 3 ) The accounts of the Trustee Committee as audited by the chartered accountant together with his`
  line `audit report shall be forwarded to the State Bar Council by that Committee and the State Bar Council may`
  line `issue such directions, as it deems fit, to the Truste e Commi ttee in respect thereof.`
  line `( 4 ) The Trustee Committee shall comply with the directions issued by the State Bar Council under`
  line `sub - section ( 3 ).`
  line `( 5 ) The Tru stee Committee shall pay from the Fund the charges for the audit as may be fixed by the`
  line `State Bar Council.`
  line `14. Powers and duties of Secretary. — The Secretary of the Trustee Committee shall —`
  line `( a ) be the chief executive authority of the Trustee Committee and responsible for carrying out its`
  line decisions;
  line `( b ) represent the Trustee Committee in all suits and pr oceedings for and against the Trustee`
  line Committee;
  line `( c ) authenticate by his signature all decisions and instruments of the Trustee Committe e;`
  line `( d ) operate b ank account of the Trustee Committe e jointly with the Chairperson;`
  line `( e ) convene meetings of the Trustee Committee and prepare minutes o f such meetings;`
  line `( f ) attend meetings of the Trustee Committee with all the nec essary records and information;`
  line `( g ) maintain such forms, registers and other records as may be prescribed from time to time and`
  line `do all correspondence rel ating to the Trustee Committee;`
  line `( h ) prepare an annual statement of business transacte d by the Trustee Committee during a`
  line `financial year;`
  line `( i ) do such other acts as are or may be directed by the Trustee Commi ttee and the State Bar`
  line Council.
  line `15. Payment of certain monies to Fund by State Bar Council. — The State Bar Council shall pay to`
  line `the Fund annually an amount equal to twenty per cent. of the enrolment fee received by it under clause ( f )`
  line `of section 24 of the Ad vocates Act, 1961 (25 of 1961 ).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
