  title `Page 8`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  sourcePage 8
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line 8
  line `CHAPTER IV`
  line `R ECOGNITION OF ANY ASSOCIATION OF ADVOCATES`
  line `16. Recognition by a State Bar Council of any association of advocates. — ( 1 ) Any association of`
  line `advocates known by any name which is registered as an association before the date of commencement of`
  line `this Act may, before the date to be notified by a State Bar Council in this behalf, apply for recognition to`
  line `the State Bar Council in s uch form as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 2 ) Any association of advocates known by any name which is registered as an association on or after`
  line `the date of commencement of this Act may, within three months from the date of its registration as an`
  line `association, apply for recognition to the State Bar Council in such for m as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 3 ) Every application for recognition under sub - section ( 1 ) or sub - section ( 2 ) shall be accompanied`
  line `by, —`
  line `( a ) a copy of the rules or bye - laws of the association;`
  line `( b ) names and addresses of off ice bearers of the association;`
  line `( c ) a list of members of the association containing the name, address, age, enrolment number and`
  line `date of enrolment with the State Bar Council and the ordinary pl ace of practice of each member.`
  line `( 4 ) The State Bar Council may, after such enquiry as it deems necessary, recognise the association`
  line `and issue a certificate of recognition in such form as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 5 ) The decision of the State Bar Council on any matter regarding recognition of an association under`
  line `sub - section ( 4 ) shall be final.`
  line `Explanation. — In this section, “registered” means registered or deemed to be registered under the`
  line `Societies Regist ration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860) or any other l aw for the time being in force.`
  line `17. Duties of State Bar Associations and State Advocates’ Associations. — ( 1 ) Every State Bar`
  line `Association and State Advocates’ Association shall, on or before the 15th day of April of every year,`
  line `furnish to the State Bar Council a list of its members as on the 31st day of March of that year.`
  line `( 2 ) Every State Bar Association and State Advocates’ Association shall inform the State Bar Council`
  line `of —`
  line `( a ) any change in the membership including admissions and re - admissions wit hin thirty d ays of`
  line `such change;`
  line `( b ) the death or other cessation of practice or voluntary suspension of practice of any of its`
  line `members within thirty days from the date of occurrence thereof;`
  line `( c ) such other matters as may be required by the State Bar Counc il from time to time.`
  line `CHAPTER V`
  line `M EMBERSHIP AND PAYMENT OUT OF A DVOCATES’ W ELFARE F UND`
  line `18. Membership in Fund. — ( 1 ) Every advocate practising, before the commencement of this Act, in`
  line `any court, tribunal or other authority in a State and being a member of a State Bar Association or a State`
  line `Advocates’ Association in t hat State, shall apply, within six months of the commencement of this Act, to`
  line `the Trustee Committee for admission as a member of the Fund, in such form a s may be prescribed.`
  line `( 2 ) Every person, —`
  line `( a ) admitted as an advocate on the roll of a State Bar Council, afte r the commencement of this`
  line Act;
  line `( b ) practising in any court, tribunal or other author ity in a State and being a member of a State`
  line `Bar Association or a State Advoca tes’ Association in that State,`
  line `shall apply, within six months of his enrolment as an advocate, to the Trustee Committee, for admission`
  line `as a member of the Fund in such form as ma y be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-9
  sectionNo (9)
