  title `Page 9`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  sourcePage 9
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line 9
  line `( 3 ) On receipt of an application under sub - section ( 1 ) or sub - section ( 2 ), the Trustee Committee shall`
  line `make such enquiry as it deems fit and either admit the applicant to the Fund or, f or reasons to be recorded`
  line `in writing, reject the application:`
  line `Provided that no order rejecting an application shall be passed unless the applicant has been given an`
  line `opportunity of being heard.`
  line `( 4 ) Every applicant shall pay an application fee of two hundred rupees along with the application to`
  line `the ac count of the Trustee Committee.`
  line `( 5 ) Every advocate, being a member of the Fund, shall pay an annual subscr iption of fifty rupees to`
  line `the Fund on or before the 31st day of March of every year:`
  line `Provided that every advocate, who makes an application under sub - section ( 1 ) or sub - section ( 2 ),`
  line `shall pay his first annual subscription within three months of his becomin g a member of the Fund:`
  line `Provided further that a senior advocate shall pay an annual subsc ription of one thousand rupees.`
  line `( 6 ) Any member of the Fund, who fails to pay the annual subscription for any year before the`
  line `31st day of March of that year, shall be liable to be removed f rom the membership in the Fund.`
  line `( 7 ) A member of the Fund removed from the membership in the Fund under sub - section ( 6 ) may be`
  line `re - admitted to the Fund, on payment of arrears along with re - admission fee of ten rupees, within six`
  line `months from the date of such removal.`
  line `( 8 ) Every member of the Fund shall, at the time of admiss ion to the membership in the Fund, make`
  line `nomination conferring on one or more of his dependants the right to receive, in the event of his death, any`
  line `amount payable t o the member under this Act.`
  line `( 9 ) If a me mber of the Fund nominates more than one person under sub - section ( 8 ), he shall specify in`
  line `the nomination, the amount or share p ayable to each of the nominees.`
  line `( 10 ) A member of the Fund may, at any time, cancel a nomination by sending a notice in wr iting to`
  line `the Trustee Committee.`
  line `( 11 ) Every member of the Fund, who cancels his nomination under sub - section ( 10 ), shall make a`
  line `fresh nomination along with r egistration fee of five rupees.`
  line `( 12 ) Every member of the Fund, whose name has been removed from the State roll under section 26 A`
  line `of the Advocates Act, 1961 (25 of 1961), or who voluntarily suspends pract ice, shall, within fifteen days`
  line `of such removal or suspension, intimate such removal or suspension to the Trustee Committee and if any`
  line `member of the Fund fails to do so without sufficient reason, the Trustee Committee may reduce, in`
  line `accordance with such pr inciples as may be prescribed, the amount payable to that member under this Act.`
  line `19. Ex gratia grant to a member of Fund. — The Trustee Committee on an application made to it by`
  line `a member of the Fund, and after being satisfied about the genuineness of the claim, may allow ex gratia`
  line `gran t to such member from the Fund —`
  line `( a ) in the case of his hospitalisation or involvi ng major surgical operation; or`
  line `( b ) if he is suffering from tuberculosis, leprosy, paralysis, cancer, unsoundness of mind or from`
  line `such other serious disease or di sability.`
  line `20. Review. — The Trustee Committee may, on its own motion or on an application received from any`
  line `person interested, within ninety days of the passing of any order by it under the provisions of t his Act,`
  line `review such order, if it was passed under any mistake, whether of fact or of law or in ignorance of any`
  line `material fact:`
  line `Provided that the Trustee Committee shall not pass any order under this section adversely affecting`
  line `any person unless such perso n has been given an opportunity of being heard.`
  line `21. Payment of amount on cessation of practice. — ( 1 ) Every advocate who has been a member of`
  line `the Fund f or a period of not less than five years shall, on his cessation of practice, be paid an amount at`
  line `the rate specified in Schedule I:`
  line `Provided that where the Trustee Committee is satisfied that a member of the Fund ceases to practice`
  line `within a period of five years from the date of his admission as a member of such Fund as a result of any`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-10
