  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  sourcePage 10
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line 10
  line `permanent disability, the Trustee Committee may pay such member an amount at th e rate specified in`
  line `Schedule I.`
  line `( 2 ) Where a member of the Fund dies before receiving the amount payable under sub - section ( 1 ), his`
  line `nominee or legal heir, as the case may be, shall be paid the amount payable to t he deceased member of the`
  line Fund.
  line `22. Restriction on alienation, attachment, etc., of interest of member in Fund. — ( 1 ) The interest`
  line `of any member in the Fund, or the right of a member of the Fund or his nominee or legal heir to receive`
  line `any am ount from the Fund, shall not be assigned, alienated, or charged and shall not be liable to`
  line `attachment under any decree or order of any cour t, tribunal or other authority.`
  line `( 2 ) No creditor shall be entitled to proceed against the Fund or the interest therein of any member of`
  line `the Fund or his nominee or legal heir.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, “creditor” includes the State or an official assignee or`
  line `official rece iver appointed under the law relating to insolvency for the time being in force.`
  line `23. Exemption from income - tax. — Notwithstanding anything contained in the Income - tax Act, 1961`
  line `(43 of 1961) or any other ena ctment for the time being in force relating to tax on income, profits or gains,`
  line `the income accrued to the Fund constituted under sub - section ( 1 ) of section 3 s hall be exempt from`
  line `income - tax.`
  line `24. Group Life Insurance for members of Fund and other benefits. — The Trustee Committee`
  line `may, for the welfa re of the members of the Fund, —`
  line `( a ) obtain, from the Life In surance Corporation of India or any other insurer, policies of Group`
  line `Insurance on the life of the members of the Fund; or`
  line `( b ) provide, in such manner as may be prescribed, for medical and educational faci lities for the`
  line `members of th e Fund and their dependants; or`
  line `( c ) provide monies to the members of the Fund for purchase of books; or`
  line `( d ) provide monies to construct or maintain common facilities for the members of the Fund:`
  line `Provided that the Trustee Committee shall spend ten per cent. of the total annual subscription`
  line `received under sub - section ( 5 ) of section 18 on the construction or maint enance of common facilities`
  line `for the members of the Fund practising in the su bordinate courts; or`
  line `( e ) provide funds for any other purpose which the Tr ustee Committee may specify; or`
  line `( f ) provide for such other benefits as may be prescribed.`
  line `25. Appeal against decision or order of Trustee Committee. — ( 1 ) An appeal against any decision`
  line `or order of the Trustee Committee shal l lie to the State Bar Council.`
  line `( 2 ) The appeal shall be in the prescribed fo rm and shall be accompanied by —`
  line `( a ) a copy of the deci sion or order appealed against;`
  line `( b ) a receipt evidencing payment of twenty - five rupees to the credit of the State Bar Council in`
  line `any of th e branches of a scheduled bank.`
  line `( 3 ) The appeal shall be filed within thirty days from the date of receipt of the deci sion or order`
  line `appealed against.`
  line `( 4 ) The decision of the State Bar Council on such appeal shall be final.`
  line `CHAPTER VI`
  line `P RINTING, DISTRIBUTION AND CANCELLATION OF STAMPS`
  line `26. Printing and distribution of Advocates’ Welfare Fund Stamps by State Bar Council. —`
  line `( 1 ) The appropriate Government shall, on a request made by the State Bar Council in this behalf, cause to`
  line `be printed and distributed Advocates’ Welfare Fund Stamps of the value of five rupees or su ch other`
  line `value, which may be prescribed, inscribing therein “Advocates’ Welfare Fund Stamp”, in such design as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-11
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Page 11`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  sourcePage 11
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line 11
  line `( 2 ) Every stamp referred to in sub - section ( 1 ) shall be of the size 2.54 c.m. by 5.08 c.m. and sold to`
  line `the advocates.`
  line `( 3 ) The custody of the stamps shall be with the State Bar Council.`
  line `( 4 ) The State Bar Council shall control the distribution and sale of the stamps through the State Bar`
  line `Associations and the State Advocate s’ Associations.`
  line `( 5 ) The State Bar Council, the State Bar Associations and the State Advocates’ Associatio ns shall`
  line `keep proper accounts of the stamps in such form a nd manner as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 6 ) The State Bar Associations and State Advocates’ Associations shall purchase the stamps from the`
  line `State Bar Cou ncil after paying the value thereof as reduced by ten per cent. of such value towards`
  line `incidental expenses.`
  line `27. Vakalatnama to bear stamps. — ( 1 ) Every advocate s hall affix stamp of a value of —`
  line `( a ) five rupees on every Vakalatnama filed by him in a District Court or a court subord inate to the`
  line `District Court;`
  line `( b ) ten rupees on every Vakalatnama filed by him in a tribunal or other authority or a High Court`
  line `or the Supreme Court:`
  line `Provided that the appropriate Government may prescribe the value of the stamps not exceeding`
  line `twenty - five rupees to be affixed under this sub - section:`
  line `Provided further that the appropriate Government may prescribe different value of the stamps to be`
  line `affixed on every Vakalatnama to be filed in a District Court, or a court subordinate to the District Court or`
  line `a tribunal or o ther authority or a H igh Court or the Supreme Court.`
  line `( 2 ) The value of the stamp shall neither be the cost in a case nor be collected in any event from the`
  line client.
  line `( 3 ) Any contravention of the provisions of sub - section ( 1 ) or sub - section ( 2 ) by any advocate shall`
  line `disentitle him either in whole or in part to the benefits of the Fund and the Trustee Committee shall report`
  line `such contravention to the State Bar Council for appropriate action.`
  line `( 4 ) Every stamp affixed on every Vakalatnama filed before a District Court or a court subordinate to`
  line `the District Court or a tribunal or other authority or a High Court o r the Supreme Court shall be cancelled`
  line `in su ch manner as may be prescribed.`
  line `CHAPTER VII`
  line `M ISCELLANEOUS`
  line `28. Certain persons not to be eligible for benefits. — No senior advocate, or a person in receipt of`
  line `pension from the Central Government or a State Government, shall be entitled to ex gratia grant under`
  line `section 19 or payment of amount on his cessation of practice under section 21 or any benefit under`
  line `clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) or clause ( c ) of section 24.`
  line `29. Protection of action taken in good faith. — No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings shall`
  line `lie against the app ropriate Government or the Trustee Committee or the Chairperson or a Member or the`
  line `Secretary of the Trustee Committee or the State Bar Council or any person for anything which is in good`
  line `faith done or intended to be done under this Ac t or the rules made th ereunder.`
  line `30. Bar of jurisdiction of civil courts. — No civil court shall have jurisdiction to settle, decide or deal`
  line `with any question or to determine any matter which is by or under this Act required to be settled, decided`
  line `or dealt with or to be determined by the Trustee Comm ittee or the State Bar Council.`
  line `31. Power to summon witnesses and take evidence. — The Trustee Committee and the State Bar`
  line `Council s hall, for the purpose of any enquiry under this Act, have the same powers as are vested in a civil`
  line `court while trying a suit under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) in respect of the following`
  line `matters, namely: —`
  line `( a ) enforcing the attendance of any p erson or examining him on oath;`
  line `( b ) requiring the discove ry and production of documents;`
  line `( c ) r eceiving evidence on affidavit;`
  line `( d ) issuing commissions fo r the examination of witnesses;`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-12
  sectionNo (12)
