  title `Page 12`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  sourcePage 12
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line 12
  line `( e ) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line `32. Power to amend Schedules I and II. — ( 1 ) The appropriate Government may, on the`
  line `recommendation of the Trustee Committee, by notification, and having due regard to the availability of`
  line `the amount in the Fund, amend the rates specified in Schedule I.`
  line `( 2 ) The Central Government may, as and when considered necessary, by n otification, amend`
  line `Schedule II.`
  line `33. Power of appropriate Government to issue directions. — ( 1 ) Without prejudice to the generality`
  line `of the foregoing provisions of this Act, the Trustee Committee shal l, in exercise of the powers or the`
  line `performance of its functions under this Act, be bound by such directions on questions of policy, other`
  line `than those relating to professional and administrative matters, as the appropriate Government may give in`
  line `writing to it from time to time:`
  line `Provided that the Trustee Committee shall, as far as practicable, be given an opportunity to express its`
  line `views before any direction i s given under this sub - section.`
  line `( 2 ) The decision of the appropriate Government, whether a question is one of policy or not, shall be`
  line final.
  line `34. Power of appropriate Government to supersede Trustee Committee. — ( 1 ) If at any time the`
  line `appropriat e Government is of the opinion —`
  line `( a ) that, on account of circumstances beyond the control of the Trustee Committee, it is unable to`
  line `discharge the fu nctions or perform the duties imposed on it by or under the provisions of this Act; or`
  line `( b ) that the Trustee Committee has persistently defaulted in complying with any direction given`
  line `by the appropriate G overnment under this Act or in the discharge of the functions or performance of`
  line `the duties imposed on it by or under the provision s of this Act; or`
  line `( c ) that circumstances exist which render it necessary i n the public interest so to do,`
  line `the appropriate Government may, by notification and for reasons to be specified therein, supersede the`
  line `Trustee Committee for such period, not exceeding six months, as may be specified in the notification and`
  line `appoint, in con sultation with the Chief Justice of the High Court having jurisdiction, a Judge of the High`
  line `Court to be the Controller of the Trustee Committee:`
  line `Provided that before issuing any such notification, the appropriate Government shall give a`
  line `reasonable opportunity to the Trustee Committee to make representations against the proposed`
  line `supersession and shall consider the representations, if any, of the Trustee Committee.`
  line `( 2 ) Upon the publication of a noti fication under sub - section ( 1 ) supe rseding the Trustee`
  line `Committee, —`
  line `( a ) the Chairperson, Members and the Secretary of the Trustee Committee shall, as from the date`
  line `of supersession, vacate their offices as such;`
  line `( b ) all powers, functions and duties which may, by or under the provisions of this Act, be`
  line `exercised or discharged by or on behalf of the Trustee Committee shall, until the Trustee Committee`
  line `is re constituted under sub - section ( 3 ), be exercised and discharged by the Controlle r of the Trustee`
  line `Committee; and`
  line `( c ) all properties and Fund owned or controlled by the Trustee Committee shall, until the Trustee`
  line `Committee is reconstituted under sub - section ( 3 ), vest in the appropriate Government.`
  line `( 3 ) On or before the ex piration of the period of supersession specified in the notification issued under`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ), the appropriate Government shall reconstitute the Trustee Committee by a fresh`
  line `appointment of its Chairperson, Members and Secretary of such Committee and in such case a person`
  line `who had vacated his office under clause ( a ) of sub - section ( 2 ) shall not be deemed to be disqualified for`
  line reappointment.
  line `( 4 ) The appropriate Government shall cause a copy of the notif ication issued under sub - section ( 1 )`
  line `and a full report of any action taken under this section and the circumstances leading to such action to be`
  line `laid before each House of Parliament or before each House of the State Legislature, where it consists of`
  line `two Ho uses or where such Legislature consists of one House, before that House, as th e case may be, at the`
  line earliest.
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-13
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Page 13`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  sourcePage 13
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line 13
  line `35. Power of Central Government to make rules. — ( 1 ) The Central Government, being the`
  line `appropriate Government, may, by notification, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) In particular, and without prejudice to the generalit y of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the periodical and annual reports to be sent under clause ( f ) of section 11;`
  line `( b ) the form and the manner in which the annual statement of accounts and annual report shall be`
  line `prepared under sub - section ( 1 ) of section 13;`
  line `( c ) the forms, registers and other records to be maintained under clause ( g ) of section 14;`
  line `( d ) the form in which an association of advocates may apply for recognition to the State Bar`
  line `Council under sub - section ( 1 ) or sub - section ( 2 ) of section 16;`
  line `( e ) the form in which a certificate of recognition shall be issued by the State Bar Council under`
  line `sub - section ( 4 ) of section 16;`
  line `( f ) the for m in which an advocate shall apply for admission as a member of the Fund under`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ) or sub - section ( 2 ) of section 18;`
  line `( g ) the principles in accordance with which the amount payable to a member of the Fund be`
  line `reduced under sub - section ( 12 ) of section 18;`
  line `( h ) the manner of providing medical and educational facilities for the members of the Fund and`
  line `their dependants under clause ( b ) of se ction 24;`
  line `( i ) the other benefits to be provided under clause ( f ) of section 24;`
  line `( j ) the form of appeal under sub - section ( 2 ) of section 25;`
  line `( k ) the value and design of stamps to be printed and distributed under sub - section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 26;`
  line `( l ) the form and the manner in which accounts of the s tamps shall be kept under sub - section ( 5 ) of`
  line `section 26;`
  line `( m ) the value of stamps not exceeding twenty - five rupees as may be prescribed under the first`
  line `proviso to sub - section ( 1 ) of section 27;`
  line `( n ) the value of stamps to be affixed on every Vakalatnama under the second proviso to`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ) of section 27;`
  line `( o ) the manner of cance llation of stamps under sub - section ( 4 ) of section 27;`
  line `( p ) any other matter which i s to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line `36. Power of State Government to ma ke rules. — ( 1 ) The State Government, being the appropriate`
  line `Government, may, by notification, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act and not`
  line `inconsistent with the rules, if any, made by the Central Government.`
  line `( 2 ) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the periodical and annual reports to be sent under clause ( f ) of section 11;`
  line `( b ) the form and the manner in which the annual statement of accounts and annual report shall be`
  line `p repared under sub - section ( 1 ) of section 13;`
  line `( c ) the forms, registers and other records to be maintained under clause ( g ) of section 14;`
  line `( d ) the form in which an association of advocates may apply for recognition to the State Bar`
  line `Council under sub - section ( 1 ) or sub - section ( 2 ) of section 16;`
  line `( e ) the form in which a certificate of recognition shall be issued by the State Bar Council under`
  line `sub - section ( 4 ) of section 16;`
  line `( f ) the form in which an advocate shall apply for admission as a member of the Fund under`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ) or sub - sect ion ( 2 ) of section 18;`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-14
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Page 14`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  sourcePage 14
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line 14
  line `( g ) the principles in accordance with which the amount payable to a member of the Fund be`
  line `reduced under sub - section ( 12 ) of section 18;`
  line `( h ) the manner of providing medical and educational facilities for the members of the Fund and`
  line `their dependants under clause ( b ) of section 24;`
  line `( i ) the other benefits to be provided under clause ( f ) of section 24;`
  line `( j ) the form of appeal under sub - section ( 2 ) of section 25;`
  line `( k ) the value and design of stamps to be printed and distributed under sub - section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 26;`
  line `( l ) the form and the manner in which accounts of the stamps shall be kept under sub - section ( 5 ) of`
  line `section 26;`
  line `( m ) the value of stamps not exceeding twenty - five rupees as may be prescribed under the first`
  line `proviso to sub - section ( 1 ) of section 27;`
  line `( n ) the value of stamps to be affixed on every Vakalatnama under the second proviso to`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ) of section 27;`
  line `( o ) the manner of cancellation of stamps under sub - section ( 4 ) of section 27;`
  line `( p ) any other matter which is to be or may be prescribed.`
  line `37. Rules and notifications to be laid before Parliament or State Legislature. — ( 1 ) Every rule`
  line `made under this Act by the Central Government and every notification issued under section 32, shall be`
  line `laid, as soon as may be after it is made or issued, before each House of Parliament, while it i s in session`
  line `for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive`
  line `sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive`
  line `sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree i n making any modification in the rule or notification or both`
  line `Houses agree that the rule or notification should not be made or issued, the rule or notification shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `u nder that rule or notification.`
  line `( 2 ) Every rule made under this Act by a State Government and every notification issued under`
  line `section 32 shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of State Legislature where`
  line `it consists of two Houses, or where such Legislature consists o f one House, before that House.`
  line `38. Saving. — The provisions of this Act shall not apply to the States in which the enactments`
  line `specified in Schedule II are applicable.`
